:''"Forum Institute" also redirects here''.
The '''Forum Minority Research Institute''' or '''Forum Institute''' (''Fórum Kisebbségkutató Intézet'' or ''Fórum Intézet'' in [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] and ''Fórum inštitút pre výskum menšín'' or ''Fórum inštitút'' in [[Slovak language|Slovak]]) is a [[Slovakia|Slovak]] [[think tank]] with its main focus on [[ethnic minorities]] living in Slovakia, especially [[Hungarians in Slovakia|Hungarians]]. The [[NGO]]'s scope of activities are the study and documenting of ethnic minorities,<ref name="about">{{cite web|url=http://foruminst.sk/en/18/about_us|title=About us|work=Forum Minority Research Institute|accessdate={{date|2012-05-22}}}}</ref> publishing these findings<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foruminst.sk/en/5/publications/0/publications_of_the_forum_minority_research_institute|title=Publications|work=Forum Minority Research Institute|accessdate={{date|2012-05-22}}}}</ref> and the keeping of a database of historical documents and photographs<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foruminst.sk/hu/13/kepeslapok/1/a_forum_kisebbsegkutato_intezet_kepeslapgyujtemenye|title=A Fórum Kisebbségkutató Intézet képeslapgyűjteménye|language=Hungarian|work=Forum Minority Research Institute|accessdate={{date|2012-05-22}}}}</ref> It also speaks out on government policy-making on a regular basis, especially when the policies affects the minorities in a negative way,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spectator.sme.sk/articles/view/38800/2/promises_not_kept_say_ethnic_hungarians_updated.html|publisher=''The Slovak Spectator''|title=Promises not kept, say ethnic Hungarians|author=Michaela Terenzani - Stanková|date={{date|2010-05-10}}|accessdate={{date|2012-05-22}}}}</ref> which sometimes triggers criticism from Slovak [[nationalism|nationalists]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.extraplus.sk/content/view/587|title=Res publica|language=Slovak|date=August 2009|author=Ľudovít Števko|publisher=''Extra Plus''|accessdate={{date|2012-05-22}}}}</ref>
== History == The institute was founded in 1996 by the [[Katedra Foundation]] and the [[Forum Foundation]] in [[Dunajská Streda]]. In 1999, two partner institutes were founded: the [[Forum Information Centre]] provides civil training and civil service, while the [[Forum Regional Development Centre]] is engaged with rural development and small area planning. Together with the Forum Minority Research Institute, these three organizations form a consortium, the [[Forum Institute (Slovakia)|Forum Institute]]. In 2002 the Forum Institute moved to [[Šamorín]], where it resides up to this day.<ref name="about" /> The president of the Institute is [[political science|political analyst]] [[László Öllös]].
