'''Save the RAH''' was a minor [[political party]] in [[South Australia]], a [[single-issue party]] with the aim of stopping the relocation of [[Adelaide]]'s main hospital, the [[Royal Adelaide Hospital]] (RAH).<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2010/02/26/2830761.htm Liberal support evident at Save RAH launch: ABC News 26 February 2010]</ref><ref>[http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/in-depth/minor-parties-big-ambitions/story-e6frebnu-1225826325410 Minor parties, big ambitions: The Advertiser 3 February 2010]</ref> It ran candidates in 11 of the 47 seats in the [[South Australian House of Assembly|House of Assembly]] at the [[South Australian state election, 2010|2010 state election]]. The party received 5,381 votes, or 0.55 percent of the statewide vote. In the [[South Australian Legislative Council|Legislative Council]], the party received 9,236 votes, or 0.97 percent. This was the highest upper house primary vote received by a party without winning a seat.<ref>[http://www.ecsa.sa.gov.au/election2010/ ECSA website] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100504104735/http://www.ecsa.sa.gov.au/election2010/ |date=2010-05-04 }}</ref> The party is no longer registered.<ref>[http://www.ecsa.sa.gov.au/parties-and-candidates/how-to-register-a-political-party/political-party-register Political party register: ECSA]</ref>
